<subSubSection id="C3109D91FFECFFF95B8C0065A540FD38" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB5CE1AFFECFFF95B8C0065A540FD38" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95B8C0065A531FD14" bold="true" box="[199,334,619,645]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Etymology.</emphasis>
The word “fortuit” in Latin means “random”. The species was collected in a random stop in the road for snack.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3109D91FFECFFF95B8C00BCA51EFC34" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB5CE1AFFECFFF95B8C00BCA51EFC34" blockId="5.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95B8C00BCA533FD5D" bold="true" box="[199,332,690,716]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Discussion.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF95A1C00BDA63FFD5C" authority="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" box="[343,576,691,717]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortuitus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95A1C00BDA63FFD5C" box="[343,576,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Campsurus fortuitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF9590100BDA6D8FD5C" bold="true" box="[586,679,691,717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24DAF73FFECFFF9590100BDA6D8FD5C" box="[586,679,691,717]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
has unusual genital characteristics, similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF95F8F00BDA51AFD60" authority="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2017" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="povilla">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95F8F00BDA1E3FD5C" box="[1220,1436,691,717]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">Campsurus povilla</emphasis>
Molineri &amp; Salles
</taxonomicName>
, but they can be distinguished by i) penis with wide base, narrowing distally in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF95FB900D9A10CFD60" authority="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" box="[1266,1395,727,753]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortuitus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95FB900D9A10CFD60" box="[1266,1395,727,753]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. fortuitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95E3000D9A4AFFC84" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24DAF73FFECFFF95E3000D9A4B5FC84" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
,
</emphasis>
while abruptly thinning basal to penile lobes in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF959B100F5A715FC84" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2017" box="[762,874,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="povilla">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF959B100F5A715FC84" box="[762,874,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. povilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; ii) main lobe of penis slender in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF95FBA00F5A10DFC84" authority="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" box="[1265,1394,763,789]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortuitus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95FBA00F5A10DFC84" box="[1265,1394,763,789]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. fortuitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95E3000F5A4B7FCA8" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24DAF73FFECFFF95E3000F5A4B7FCA8" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, while robust in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF95ACC0111A588FCA8" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2017" box="[391,503,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="povilla">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95ACC0111A588FCA8" box="[391,503,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. povilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; iii) main lobe of penis with inner margin apex curved outwards in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF95FB80111A10CFCA8" authority="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" box="[1267,1395,799,825]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortuitus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95FB80111A10CFCA8" box="[1267,1395,799,825]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. fortuitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95E300111A4B7FCCC" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24DAF73FFECFFF95E300111A4B7FCCC" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, while apex rounded in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF95A9B014DA642FCCC" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2017" box="[464,573,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="povilla">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95A9B014DA642FCCC" box="[464,573,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. povilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; iv) secondary lobe of penis completely reduced in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF95F3E014DA08BFCCC" authority="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" box="[1141,1268,835,861]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortuitus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95F3E014DA08BFCCC" box="[1141,1268,835,861]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. fortuitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95FB2014DA12EFCCC" bold="true" box="[1273,1361,835,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24DAF73FFECFFF95FB2014DA12EFCCC" box="[1273,1361,835,861]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, while greatly reduced but clearly present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF959750169A6D2FC10" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2017" box="[574,685,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="povilla">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF959750169A6D2FC10" box="[574,685,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. povilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; v) pedestal in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF958120169A7A6FC10" authority="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada, 2022" authorityName="Cruz &amp; Molineri &amp; Hamada" authorityYear="2022" box="[857,985,871,897]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fortuitus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF958120169A7A6FC10" box="[857,985,871,897]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. fortuitus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF958AB0169A045FC10" bold="true" box="[992,1082,871,897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24DAF73FFECFFF958AB0169A045FC10" box="[992,1082,871,897]" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
with inner projection straighter than in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0AB599FFECFFF95BA00185A525FC34" authorityName="Molineri &amp; Salles" authorityYear="2017" box="[235,346,907,933]" class="Insecta" family="Polymitarcyidae" genus="Campsurus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Ephemeroptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="440" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="povilla">
<emphasis id="B97E1208FFECFFF95BA00185A525FC34" box="[235,346,907,933]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="440">C. povilla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
